critter_settings.name: <link="HATCHHARD">Custom Hatchling</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A doofy little Stone Hatchling.

It matures into an adult Hatch morph, the <link="HATCHHARD">Stone Hatch</link>, which loves nibbling on various rocks and metals.

critter_settings.name: <link="HATCHHARD">Custom Hatch</link>
critter_settings.desc: Stone Hatches excrete solid <link="CARBON">Coal</link> as waste and enjoy burrowing into the ground.

critter_settings.name: Sweepy
critter_settings.desc:
An automated sweeping robot.

Picks up both <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid</link> and <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> debris and stores it in a <link="SWEEPBOTSTATION">Sweepy Dock</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="LIGHTBUGPURPLE">Royal Nymph</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A chubby baby <link="LIGHTBUGPURPLE">Shine Bug</link>.

This one is a Royal morph.

critter_settings.name: <link="MOLE">Shove Vole</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Shove Voles are burrowing critters that eat the <link="REGOLITH">Regolith</link> collected on terrestrial surfaces.

They cannot burrow through <link="REFINEDMETAL">Refined Metals</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="MOLE">Vole Pup</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Shove Voles are burrowing critters that eat the <link="REGOLITH">Regolith</link> collected on terrestrial surfaces.

They cannot burrow through <link="REFINEDMETAL">Refined Metals</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="MOO">Gassy Moo</link>
critter_settings.desc: Moos are extraterrestrial critters that feed on <link="GASGRASS">Gas Grass</link> and excrete <link="METHANE">Natural Gas</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="OILFLOATER">Slickster</link>
critter_settings.desc: Slicksters are slimy critters that consume <link="CARBONDIOXIDE">Carbon Dioxide</link> and exude <link="CRUDEOIL">Crude Oil</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="OILFLOATER">Slickster Larva</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A goopy little Slickster Larva.

One day it will grow into an adult <link="OILFLOATER">Slickster</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="OILFLOATERDECOR">Longhair Slickster</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Longhair Slicksters are friendly critters that consume <link="OXYGEN">Oxygen</link> and thrive in close contact with Duplicant companions.

Longhairs have extremely beautiful and luxurious coats.

critter_settings.name: <link="OILFLOATERDECOR">Longhair Larva</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A snuggly little Longhair Larva.

One day it will grow into an adult Slickster morph, the <link="OILFLOATERDECOR">Longhair Slickster</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="LIGHTBUGPURPLE">Royal Bug</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Shine Bugs emit a soft <link="LIGHT">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Royal morph has been turned purple through selective breeding.

critter_settings.name: <link="OILFLOATERHIGHTEMP">Molten Slickster</link>
critter_settings.desc: Molten Slicksters are slimy critters that consume <link="CARBONDIOXIDE">Carbon Dioxide</link> and exude <link="PETROLEUM">Petroleum</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="PACUCLEANER">Gulp Fish</link>
critter_settings.desc: Every organism in the known universe finds the Pacu extremely delicious.

critter_settings.name: <link="PACUCLEANER">Gulp Fry</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A wriggly little Gulp Fry.

In time, it will mature into an adult <link="PACUCLEANER">Gulp Fish</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="PACU">Pacu</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Pacus are aquatic creatures that cannot live outside of <link="WATER">Water</link> or <link="DIRTYWATER">Contaminated Water</link>.

Every organism in the known universe finds the Pacu extremely delicious.

critter_settings.name: <link="PACU">Pacu Fry</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A wriggly little Pacu Fry.

In time, it will mature into an adult <link="PACU">Pacu</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="PACUTROPICAL">Tropical Pacu</link>
critter_settings.desc: Every organism in the known universe finds the Pacu extremely delicious.

critter_settings.name: <link="PACUTROPICAL">Tropical Fry</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A wriggly little Tropical Fry.

In time it will mature into an adult Pacu morph, the <link="PACUTROPICAL">Tropical Pacu</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFTALPHA">Puft Prince</link>
critter_settings.desc: The Puft Prince is a lazy critter that excretes little <link="SOLID">Solid</link> lumps of whatever it has been breathing.

critter_settings.name: <link="OILFLOATERHIGHTEMP">Molten Larva</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A goopy little Molten Larva.

One day it will grow into an adult Slickster morph, the <link="OILFLOATERHIGHTEMP">Molten Slickster</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="LIGHTBUGPINK">Coral Nymph</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A chubby baby <link="LIGHTBUGPINK">Shine Bug</link>.

This one is a Coral morph.

critter_settings.name: <link="LIGHTBUGPINK">Coral Bug</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Shine Bugs emit a soft <link="LIGHT">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Coral morph has been turned pink through selective breeding.

critter_settings.name: <link="LIGHTBUGORANGE">Sun Nymph</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A chubby baby <link="LIGHTBUGORANGE">Shine Bug</link>.

This one is a Sun morph.

critter_settings.name: <link="CRAB">Pokeshell Spawn</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A snippy little Pokeshell Spawn.

In time it will mature into a fully grown <link="CRAB">Pokeshell</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="DRECKO">Drecko</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Dreckos are nonhostile critters that graze only on live <link="BASICSINGLEHARVESTPLANT">Mealwood Plants</link>.

Their backsides are covered in thick woolly fibers that only grow in <link="HYDROGEN">Hydrogen</link> climates.

critter_settings.name: <link="DRECKO">Drecklet</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A little, bug-eyed Drecklet.

In time it will mature into a fully grown <link="DRECKO">Drecko</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="DRECKOPLASTIC">Glossy Drecko</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Glossy Dreckos are nonhostile critters that graze only on live <link="BASICSINGLEHARVESTPLANT">Mealwood Plants</link>.

Their backsides are covered in bioplastic scales that only grow in <link="HYDROGEN">Hydrogen</link> climates.

critter_settings.name: <link="DRECKOPLASTIC">Glossy Drecklet</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A bug-eyed little Glossy Drecklet.

In time it will mature into an adult Drecko morph, the <link="DRECKOPLASTIC">Glossy Drecko</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="GLOM">Morb</link>
critter_settings.desc: Morbs are attracted to unhygienic conditions and frequently excrete bursts of <link="CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN">Polluted Oxygen</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="HATCH">Hatchling</link>
critter_settings.desc:
An innocent little Hatchling.

In time, it will mature into an adult <link="HATCH">Hatch</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="HATCHHARD">Stone Hatchling</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A doofy little Stone Hatchling.

It matures into an adult Hatch morph, the <link="HATCHHARD">Stone Hatch</link>, which loves nibbling on various rocks and metals.

critter_settings.name: <link="HATCHMETAL">Smooth Hatchling</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A doofy little Smooth Hatchling.

It matures into an adult Hatch morph, the <link="HATCHMETAL">Smooth Hatch</link>, which loves nibbling on different types of metals.

critter_settings.name: <link="HATCHVEGGIE">Sage Hatchling</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A doofy little Sage Hatchling.

It matures into an adult Hatch morph, the <link="HATCHVEGGIE">Sage Hatch</link>, which loves nibbling on organic materials.

critter_settings.name: <link="LIGHTBUGBLACK">Abyss Bug</link>
critter_settings.desc: This Shine Bug emits no <link="LIGHT">Light</link>, but it makes up for it by having an excellent personality.

critter_settings.name: <link="LIGHTBUGBLACK">Abyss Nymph</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A chubby baby <link="LIGHTBUGBLACK">Shine Bug</link>.

This one is an Abyss morph.

critter_settings.desc:

The light of the Azure morph has been turned blue through selective breeding.

critter_settings.desc:
A chubby baby <link="LIGHTBUGBLUE">Shine Bug</link>.

This one is an Azure morph.

critter_settings.desc: Shine Bugs emit a soft <link="LIGHT">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

critter_settings.desc: A chubby baby <link="LIGHTBUG">Shine Bug</link>.

critter_settings.desc:
Shine Bugs emit a soft <link="LIGHT">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.

The light of the Sun morph has been turned orange through selective breeding.

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFTBLEACHSTONE">Squeaky Puft</link>
critter_settings.desc: Squeaky Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete lumps of <link="BLEACHSTONE">Bleachstone</link> with each breath.

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFTBLEACHSTONE">Squeaky Puftlet</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A frazzled little Squeaky Puftlet.

One day it will grow into an adult Puft morph, the <link="PUFTBLEACHSTONE">Squeaky Puft</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFTALPHA">Puftlet Prince</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A gassy little Puftlet Prince.

One day it will grow into an adult Puft morph, the <link="PUFTALPHA">Puft Prince</link>.

It seems a bit snobby...

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFT">Puftlet</link>
critter_settings.desc: Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete lumps of <link="SLIMEMOLD">Slime</link> with each breath.

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFT">Puft</link>
critter_settings.desc: Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete lumps of <link="SLIMEMOLD">Slime</link> with each breath.

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFTOXYLITE">Dense Puft</link>
critter_settings.desc: Dense Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete condensed <link="OXYROCK">Oxylite</link> with each breath.

critter_settings.name: <link="PUFTOXYLITE">Dense Puftlet</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A stocky little Dense Puftlet.

One day it will grow into an adult Puft morph, the <link="PUFTOXYLITE">Dense Puft</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="SQUIRREL">Pip</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Pips are pesky, nonhostile critters that subsist on the branches of <link="FORESTTREE">Arbor Trees</link>.

They are known to bury <link="PLANTS">Seeds</link> in the ground whenever they can find a suitable area with enough space.

critter_settings.name: <link="SQUIRREL">Pipsqueak</link>
critter_settings.desc:
A little purring Pipsqueak.

In time it will mature into a fully grown <link="SQUIRREL">Pip</link>.

critter_settings.name: <link="HATCHHARD">Stone Hatch</link>
critter_settings.desc: Stone Hatches excrete solid <link="CARBON">Coal</link> as waste and enjoy burrowing into the ground.

critter_settings.name: <link="HATCH">Hatch</link>
critter_settings.desc: Hatches excrete solid <link="CARBON">Coal</link> as waste and may be uncovered by digging up Buried Objects.

critter_settings.name: <link="CRAB">Pokeshell</link>
critter_settings.desc:
Pokeshells are nonhostile critters that eat <link="TOXICSAND">Polluted Dirt</link> and <link="COMPOST">Rot Piles</link>.

The shells they leave behind after molting can be crushed into <link="LIME">Lime</link>.

critter_settings.desc: Smooth Hatches enjoy burrowing into the ground and excrete <link="REFINEDMETAL">Refined Metal</link> when fed <link="RAWMETAL">Metal Ore</link>.
